  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Advanced Optics",
      "text": "The UVC-G6-INS-W is equipped with a 1/1.8\" 8MP CMOS sensor, delivering ultra-high-definition 4K video at 3840 x 2160 resolution. Its fixed focal length lens provides a wide field of view: horizontal 109.9°, vertical 56.7°, and diagonal 134.1°, ensuring comprehensive area coverage. The camera supports a maximum frame rate of 30 FPS, capturing smooth and detailed footage. Advanced image settings include brightness, contrast, sharpness, saturation, white balance, exposure control, 2D and 3D noise reduction, motion-based noise reduction, masking, text overlay, and HDR, allowing for precise image optimization in various lighting conditions."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Robust Construction and Seamless Integration",
      "text": "Designed for outdoor use, the UVC-G6-INS-W boasts an IPX5-rated weatherproof enclosure, protecting it against water ingress. Its IK04 impact resistance rating ensures durability against vandalism. The camera operates reliably in temperatures ranging from -20°C to 40°C and humidity levels up to 90% (non-condensing). It supports dual-band WiFi (802.11 a/b/g/n/ac) and Bluetooth for flexible network connectivity. Power is supplied via a 5V 2A USB adapter (included), with an optional PoE to USB-C adapter available separately. Mounting options include wall installations, with the necessary hardware provided, facilitating versatile deployment scenarios. The G6 Instant integrates seamlessly with the UniFi Protect application suite, offering centralized management and real-time monitoring through web and mobile platforms. It features a 10/100 Mbps Ethernet interface for network connectivity and includes a built-in microphone and speaker for two-way audio communication. The camera's firmware supports advanced features such as HDR imaging and smart detection analytics, enhancing situational awareness. Compliance with NDAA regulations ensures suitability for government and enterprise deployments. The package includes the camera unit, mounting hardware, and installation guide, facilitating straightforward setup and integration into existing security systems."
    }
  ],
